The paper proposes a novel Markov Random Field (MRF) model for image modeling that uses fully-connected neurons to express complex interactions among pixels. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper combines the expressive power of deep neural networks and the cyclic dependency structure of MRF, indicating that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions theoretical analysis and approximated feed-forward networks, which suggest that it may belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses low-level vision tasks, indicating that it may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
